| 0.5h |\n29: | 4.2.3 | Define route constants and path patterns | Constants usable in tests and handlers | 0.5h |\n30: \n31: **Deliverable:** Core types defined and compile.\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## ST-4.3 — JWT Manager\n36: \n37: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n38: |---|------|--------------|------|\n39: | 4.3.1 | Implement `JWTManager` struct with RSA key pair | Struct compiles with private/public keys | 1h |\n40: | 4.3.2 | Implement `GenerateToken()` with RS256 signing | Unit test: token parses and signature validates | 2h |\n41: | 4.3.3 | Implement `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret()` for K8s persistence | Unit test with fake K8s client: keys stored/loaded correctly | 2h |\n42: | 4.3.4 | Implement key generation on startup if no keys exist | Test: new keys generated, valid RSA 2048-bit | 1h |\n43: | 4.3.5 | Add JWT constants (IdentitySecretName, IdentityNamespace, expiration) | Constants verified in tests | 0.5h |\n44: \n45: **Deliverable:** JWT manager generates valid RS256 tokens, persists to K8s secrets.\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ## ST-4.4 — Session Manager\n50: \n51: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n52: |---|------|--------------|------|\n53: | 4.4.1 | Implement `manager` struct implementing `SessionManager` | Struct compiles with storeClient and workloadMgrAddr | 1h |\n54: | 4.4.2 | Implement `GetSandboxBySession()` — cache hit path | Unit test: session found in store, returns SandboxInfo | 2h |\n55: | 4.4.3 | Implement `GetSandboxBySession()` — cache miss, create via Workload Manager | Unit test: POST to mock WM, parses response correctly | 3h |\n56: | 4.4.4 | Handle Workload Manager errors (non-2xx responses) | Unit test: 404 returns wrapped error, 500 returns wrapped error | 1.5h |\n57: | 4.4.5 | Implement `mapKindToEndpoint()` helper | Unit test: all kind→endpoint mappings correct | 0.5h |\n58: \n59: **Deliverable:** Session manager resolves sessions, falls back to Workload Manager on miss.\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ## ST-4.5 — Reverse Proxy Core\n64: \n65: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n66: |---|------|--------------|------|\n67: | 4.5.1 | Implement `createReverseProxy()` with httputil | Unit test: proxy created with correct target URL | 1.5h |\n68: | 4.5.2 | Implement path normalization in Director | Unit test: paths starting without \"/\" get \"/\" prepended | 1h |\n69: | 4.5.3 | Implement forwarding headers (X-Forwarded-Host, X-Forwarded-Proto, X-Forwarded-For) | Unit test: all headers set correctly | 1h |\n70: | 4.5.4 | Implement `ModifyResponse` to inject `x-agentcube-session-id` header | Unit test: response has session ID header | 1h |\n71: | 4.5.5 | Implement `ErrorHandler` with proper error mapping | Unit test: connection refused → 502, timeout → 504 | 1.5h |\n72: | 4.5.6 | Implement upstream URL selection from EntryPoints | Unit test: matches path prefix, falls back to first entry | 2h |\n73: \n74: **Deliverable:** Reverse proxy handles HTTP/1.1 and HTTP/2 passthrough correctly.\n75: \n76: ---\n77: \n78: ## ST-4.6 — HTTP Handlers\n79: \n80: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n81: |---|------|--------------|------|\n82: | 4.6.1 | Implement `handleAgentInvoke()` GET/POST | Integration test: proxy to sandbox, returns response | 2h |\n83: | 4.6.2 | Implement `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke()` GET/POST | Integration test: proxy to sandbox, returns response | 1h |\n84: | 4.6.3 | Implement session ID extraction from `x-agentcube-session-id` header | Unit test: header parsed, empty string if missing | 0.5h |\n85: | 4.6.4 | Implement JWT injection into Authorization header | Unit test: Bearer token present in upstream request | 1.5h |\n86: | 4.6.5 | Handle session resolution errors (404, 500) | Unit test: proper HTTP status codes returned | 1h |\n87: \n88: **Deliverable:** Handlers route requests, inject JWT, return proper errors.\n89: \n90: ---\n91: \n92: ## ST-4.7 — Middleware\n93: \n94: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n95: |---|------|--------------|------|\n96: | 4.7.1 | Implement `concurrencyLimitMiddleware()` with semaphore | Unit test: allows up to limit, rejects with 429 when full | 2h |\n97: | 4.7.2 | Verify semaphore releases after request completes | Test: subsequent requests succeed after completion | 1h |\n98: | 4.7.3 | Configure Gin Logger middleware | Integration test: structured logs emitted | 0.5h |\n99: | 4.7.4 | Configure Gin Recovery middleware | Integration test: panic recovers, 500 returned | 1h |\n100: \n101: **Deliverable:** Middleware limits concurrency, logs, recovers from panics.\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ## ST-4.8 — Health Endpoints\n106: \n107: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n108: |---|------|--------------|------|\n109: | 4.8.1 | Implement `handleHealthLive()` liveness probe | `curl /health/live` returns 200 {\"status\":\"alive\"} | 0.5h |\n110: | 4.8.2 | Implement `handleHealthReady()` readiness probe | Returns 200 when ready, 503 when sessionManager nil | 1h |\n111: | 4.8.3 | Register health routes (no middleware) | Integration test: health endpoints accessible | 0.5h |\n112: \n113: **Deliverable:** Health endpoints work for K8s probes.\n114: \n115: ---\n116: \n117: ## ST-4.9 — Metrics\n118: \n119: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n120: |---|------|--------------|------|\n121: | 4.9.1 | Define Prometheus counters and histograms (proxyRequestsTotal, proxyRequestDuration, sessionCreationsTotal, concurrentRequests) | Metrics compile, registered | 1h |\n122: | 4.9.2 | Instrument proxy requests with status and kind labels | Integration test: metrics incremented correctly | 1.5h |\n123: | 4.9.3 | Instrument session creation with kind and result labels | Unit test: counter incremented on create | 1h |\n124: | 4.9.4 | Expose `/metrics` endpoint | `curl /metrics` returns Prometheus format | 0.5h |\n125: \n126: **Deliverable:** Metrics endpoint exposes router metrics.\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: ## ST-4.10 — Server Lifecycle\n131: \n132: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n133: |---|------|--------------|------|\n134: | 4.10.1 | Implement `NewServer()` constructor | Returns configured server instance | 1h |\n135: | 4.10.2 | Implement `SetupRoutes()` with all endpoints | Route table matches design spec | 1.5h |\n136: | 4.10.3 | Implement `Start()` with HTTP/2 support | Server starts, listens on configured port | 1h |\n137: | 4.10.4 | Implement `Shutdown()` with graceful timeout | Context cancelled, connections drained within timeout | 1.5h |\n138: | 4.10.5 | Configure shared HTTP transport (MaxIdleConnsPerHost, IdleConnTimeout) | Transport config verified in tests | 1h |\n139: \n140: **Deliverable:** Server starts, routes, stops gracefully.\n141: \n142: ---\n143: \n144: ## ST-4.11 — Main Entry Point\n145: \n146: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n147: |---|------|--------------|------|\n148: | 4.11.1 | Create `cmd/router/main.go` with flag parsing | `go build ./cmd/router/...` produces binary | 1h |\n149: | 4.11.2 | Implement signal handling (SIGTERM, SIGINT) | Test: signal triggers graceful shutdown | 1h |\n150: | 4.11.3 | Wire dependencies (session store client, JWT manager) | Integration test: all components initialized | 1.5h |\n151: | 4.11.4 | Add klog initialization for structured logging | Logs appear in structured format | 0.5h |\n152: \n153: **Deliverable:** Binary runs, handles signals, logs structured.\n154: \n155: ---\n156: \n157: ## ST-4.12 — Integration & E2E Tests\n158: \n159: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n160: |---|------|--------------|------|\n161: | 4.12.1 | Write integration test: full proxy flow | Request → Router → Mock Sandbox → Response | 3h |\n162: | 4.12.2 | Write integration test: session creation on cache miss | No session → WM called → session stored | 2h |\n163: | 4.12.3 | Write integration test: WebSocket upgrade passthrough | WebSocket handshake proxied correctly | 2h |\n164: | 4.12.4 | Write integration test: concurrent request handling | 100 concurrent requests, all succeed | 2h |\n165: | 4.12.5 | Run race detector: `go test -race ./pkg/router/...` | 