{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869722679,"sessionID":"ses_285eaae91ffe60KoaOG4ouBHAC","part":{"id":"prt_d7a15779b001KumJt9sb9QsHB2","messageID":"msg_d7a1566f0001C2cswrXVx5FE0m","sessionID":"ses_285eaae91ffe60KoaOG4ouBHAC","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-013/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-013/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-013 Tasks: Redis 存储实现 (Redis Storage Implementation)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: - **AR:** AR-013\n5: - **Module:** pkg/store\n6: - **Language:** Go\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Status:** Stage ST-3 (Design) Completed\n9: - **Base Spec:** AR-012 (Store Interface Definition)\n10: \n11: ## Task Checklist\n12: \n13: ### T1: Redis Store Implementation - Core Structure [PENDING]\n14: - [ ] Create `pkg/store/redis.go` with `redisStore` struct\n15: - [ ] Define `redisOptions` struct with `Addr` and `Password` fields\n16: - [ ] Implement `newRedisStore()` constructor with environment parsing\n17: - [ ] Implement `makeRedisOptions()` for `REDIS_ADDR`, `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED`\n18: - [ ] Add `sessionKey()` helper method for key construction (`session:` + sessionID)\n19: - **Verification:** File compiles; `go build ./pkg/store/...` succeeds\n20: - **Files:** `pkg/store/redis.go`\n21: \n22: ### T2: Redis Store - Ping Method [PENDING]\n23: - [ ] Implement `Ping(ctx context.Context) error`\n24: - [ ] Issue `PING` command via go-redis/v9 client\n25: - [ ] Validate response is exactly `\"PONG\"`\n26: - [ ] Return error on connection failure or unexpected response\n27: - **Verification:** Unit test passes with mocked Redis client\n28: - **Files:** `pkg/store/redis.go`, `pkg/store/redis_test.go`\n29: \n30: ### T3: Redis Store - GetSandboxBySessionID [PENDING]\n31: - [ ] Implement `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n32: - [ ] Validate empty sessionID returns error before querying\n33: - [ ] Execute `GET session:{id}` command\n34: - [ ] Translate `redisv9.Nil` to `ErrNotFound`\n35: - [ ] Unmarshal JSON response to `*types.SandboxInfo`\n36: - [ ] Return wrapped error on JSON parse failure\n37: - **Verification:** Test missing key returns `ErrNotFound`; test valid session returns data\n38: - **Files:** `pkg/store/redis.go`, `pkg/store/redis_test.go`\n39: \n40: ### T4: Redis Store - StoreSandbox [PENDING]\n41: - [ ] Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n42: - [ ] Validate nil sandbox returns error (no Redis commands)\n43: - [ ] Validate empty `SessionID` returns error (no Redis commands)\n44: - [ ] Validate zero `ExpiresAt` returns error (no Redis commands)\n45: - [ ] Marshal sandbox to JSON\n46: - [ ] Use Pipeline for atomic operation:\n47:   - `SETNX session:{id} {json}`\n48:   - `ZADD session:expiry {ExpiresAt.Unix()} {id}`\n49:   - `ZADD session:last_activity {Now.Unix()} {id}`\n50: - [ ] Check `SETNX` result; if false, return \"session already exists\" error\n51: - [ ] Return pipeline execution error if any command fails\n52: - **Verification:** Test validation errors (no Redis calls); test atomic success; test duplicate session\n53: - **Files:** `pkg/store/redis.go`, `pkg/store/redis_test.go`\n54: \n55: ### T5: Redis Store - UpdateSandbox [PENDING]\n56: - [ ] Implement `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n57: - [ ] Validate nil sandbox returns error\n58: - [ ] Validate empty `SessionID` returns error\n59: - [ ] Marshal sandbox to JSON\n60: - [ ] Execute `SET session:{id} {json} XX` (key must exist)\n61: - [ ] If result is false, return \"key not exists\" error\n62: - [ ] Do NOT modify expiry or activity ZSETs\n63: - **Verification:** Test missing key returns error; test successful update\n64: - **Files:** `pkg/store/redis.go`, `pkg/store/redis_test.go`\n65: \n66: ### T6: Redis Store - DeleteSandboxBySessionID [PENDING]\n67: - [ ] Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) error`\n68: - [ ] Validate empty sessionID returns error (no Redis commands)\n69: - [ ] Use Pipeline for atomic operation:\n70:   - `DEL session:{id}`\n71:   - `ZREM session:expiry {id}`\n72:   - `ZREM session:last_activity {id}`\n73: - [ ] Return pipeline execution error\n74: - **Verification:** Test deletion removes all keys; test empty ID validation\n75: - **Files:** `pkg/store/redis.go`, `pkg/store/redis_test.go`\n76: \n77: ### T7: Redis Store - ListExpiredSandboxes [PENDING]\n78: - [ ] Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n79: - [ ] Return `nil, nil` if limit <= 0 (no Redis query)\n80: - [ ] Execute `ZRANGE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix()} BYSCORE LIMIT 0 {limit}`\n81: - [ ] Call `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` helper to fetch full documents\n82: - **Verification:** Test limit=0 returns empty; test expired sessions returned\n83: - **Files:** `pkg/store/redis.go`, `pkg/store/redis_test.go`\n84: \n85: ### T8: Redis Store - ListInactiveSandboxes [PENDING]\n86: - [ ] Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n87: - [ ] Return `nil, nil` if limit <= 0 (no Redis query)\n88: - [ ] Execute `ZRANGE session:last_activity -inf {before.Unix()} BYSCORE LIMIT 0 {limit}`\n89: - [ ] Call `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` helper to fetch full documents\n90: - **Verification:** Test limit=0 returns empty; test inactive sessions returned\n91: - **Files:** `pkg/store/redis.go`, `pkg/store/redis_test.go`\n92: \n93: ### T9: Redis Store - Helper: loadSandboxesBySessionIDs [PENDING]\n94: - [ ] Implement `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, sessionIDs []string) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n95: - [ ] Return empty slice if sessionIDs is empty\n96: - [ ] Construct keys using `sessionKey()` for each sessionID\n97: - [ ] Execute `MGET` for all keys\n98: - [ ] Iterate results and skip nil/invalid entries (orphan tolerance)\n99: - [ ] Unmarshal valid JSON to `*types.SandboxInfo`\n100: - [ ] Return slice of valid sandboxes\n101: - **Verification:** Test orphaned entries are skipped; test batch loading\n102: - **Files:** `pkg/store/redis.go`, `pkg/store/redis_test.go`\n103: \n104: ### T10: Redis Store - UpdateSessionLastActivity [PENDING]\n105: - [ ] Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID string, at time.Time) error`\n106: - [ ] Validate empty sessionID returns error (no Redis query)\n107: - [ ] Execute `EXISTS session:{id}` to verify session exists\n108: - [ ] Return `ErrNotFound` if exists == 0\n109: - [ ] If `at.IsZero()`, use `time.Now()`\n110: - [ ] Execute `ZADD session:last_activity {at.Unix()} {sessionID}`\n111: - **Verification:** Test missing session returns `ErrNotFound`; test zero time uses now\n112: - **Files:** `pkg/store/redis.go`, `pkg/store/redis_test.go`\n113: \n114: ### T11: Redis Store - Close [PENDING]\n115: - [ ] Implement `Close() error`\n116: - [ ] Call `s.cli.Close()` on Redis client\n117: - [ ] Return the error from Close()\n118: - **Verification:** Test Close releases connection\n119: - **Files:** `pkg/store/redis.go`, `pkg/store/redis_test.go`\n120: \n121: ### T12: Valkey Store Implementation - Core Structure [PENDING]\n122: - [ ] Create `pkg/store/valkey.go` with `valkeyStore` struct\n123: - [ ] Define `valkeyOptions` struct with `InitAddress []string`, `Password`, `DisableCache`, `ForceSingleClient`\n124: - [ ] Implement `newValkeyStore()` constructor\n125: - [ ] Implement `makeValkeyOptions()` for Valkey environment parsing\n126: - **Verification:** File compiles; `go build ./pkg/store/...` succeeds\n127: - **Files:** `pkg/store/valkey.go`\n128: \n129: ### T13: Valkey Store - Ping Method [PENDING]\n130: - [ ] Implement `Ping(ctx context.Context) error`\n131: - [ ] Build command using `B().Ping().Build()`\n132: - [ ] Validate response is exactly `\"PONG\"`\n133: - **Verification:** Unit test passes with mocked Valkey client\n134: - **Files:** `pkg/store/valkey.go`, `pkg/store/valkey_test.go`\n135: \n136: ### T14: Valkey Store - GetSandboxBySessionID [PENDING]\n137: - [ ] Implement `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n138: - [ ] Validate empty sessionID returns error before querying\n139: - [ ] Build GET command using valkey-go builder\n140: - [ ] Detect `IsValkeyNil` error and translate to `ErrNotFound`\n141: - [ ] Unmarshal JSON response\n142: - **Verification:** Test missing key returns `ErrNotFound`\n143: - **Files:** `pkg/store/valkey.go`, `pkg/store/valkey_test.go`\n144: \n145: ### T15: Valkey Store - StoreSandbox [PENDING]\n146: - [ ] Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n147: - [ ] Validate nil sandbox, empty SessionID, zero ExpiresAt (no Valkey commands)\n148: - [ ] Marshal sandbox to JSON\n149: - [ ] Use `DoMulti` for atomic operation:\n150:   - `SET session:{id} {json} NX`\n151:   - `ZADD session:expiry {expires_unix} {id}`\n152:   - `ZADD session:last_activity {now_unix} {id}`\n153: - [ ] Check first result for \"OK\"; if not, return \"session already exists\"\n154: - **Verification:** Test validation; test atomic success; test duplicate\n155: - **Files:** `pkg/store/valkey.go`, `pkg/store/valkey_test.go`\n156: \n157: ### T16: Valkey Store - UpdateSandbox [PENDING]\n158: - [ ] Implement `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n159: - [ ] Validate nil sandbox, empty SessionID\n160: - [ ] Marshal sandbox to JSON\n161: - [ ] Execute `SET session:{id} {json} XX`\n162: - [ ] If result is not \"OK\", return \"key not exists\" error\n163: - [ ] Do NOT modify ZSETs\n164: - **Verification:** Test missing key returns error\n165: - **Files:** `pkg/store/valkey.go`, `pkg/store/valkey_test.go`\n166: \n167: ### T17: Valkey Store - DeleteSandboxBySessionID [PENDING]\n168: - [ ] Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) error`\n169: - [ ] Validate empty sessionID returns error\n170: - [ ] Use `DoMulti` for atomic operation:\n171:   - `DEL session:{id}`\n172:   - `ZREM session:expiry {id}`\n173:   - `ZREM session:last_activity {id}`\n174: - **Verification:** Test deletion removes all keys\n175: - **Files:** `pkg/store/valkey.go`, `pkg/store/valkey_test.go`\n176: \n177: ### T18: Valkey Store - List Methods [PENDING]\n178: - [ ] Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n179: - [ ] Return `nil, nil` if limit <= 0\n180: - [ ] Execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix()} LIMIT 0 {limit}`\n181: - [ ] Load full documents via batch GET\n182: - [ ] Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes()` similarly using `session:last_activity`\n183: - [ ] Implement valkey-specific `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` helper\n184: - **Verification:** Test listing with orphaned entry tolerance\n185: - **Files:** `pkg/store/valkey.go`, `pkg/store/valkey_test.go`\n186: \n187: ### T19: Valkey Store - UpdateSessionLastActivity [PENDING]\n188: - [ ] Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID string, at time.Time) error`\n189: - [ ] Validate empty sessionID\n190: - [ ] Execute `EXISTS session:{id}`; return `ErrNotFound` if not exists\n191: - [ ] If `at.IsZero()`, use `time.Now()`\n192: - [ ] Execute `ZADD session:last_activity {at.Unix()} {sessionID}`\n193: - **Verification:** Test missing session returns `ErrNotFound`\n194: - **Files:** `pkg/store/valkey.go`, `pkg/store/valkey_test.go`\n195: \n196: ### T20: Valkey Store - Close [PENDING]\n197: - [ ] Implement `Close() error`\n198: - [ ] Call `s.cli.Close()` on Valkey client\n199: - [ ] Return nil on success\n200: - **Verification:** Test Close releases connection\n201: - **Files:** `pkg/store/valkey.go`, `pkg/store/valkey_test.go`\n202: \n203: ### T21: Singleton Pattern & Provider Selection [PENDING]\n204: - [ ] Create `pkg/store/singleton.go`\n205: - [ ] Implement `initStore()` with `STORE_TYPE` case-insensitive parsing\n206: - [ ] Default to `\"redis\"` if `STORE_TYPE` unset\n207: - [ ] Implement `newRedisStore()` call for `redis` type\n208: - [ ] Implement `newValkeyStore()` call for `valkey` type\n209: - [ ] Return error for unsupported store type\n210: - [ ] Implement `Storage()` with `sync.Once` singleton pattern\n211: - [ ] Call `klog.Fatalf` on initialization failure\n212: - **Verification:** Test concurrent access returns same instance; test provider selection\n213: - **Files:** `pkg/store/singleton.go`, `pkg/store/singleton_test.go`\n214: \n215: ### T22: Unit Tests - Redis Implementation [PENDING]\n216: - [ ] Test `Ping()` success and failure scenarios\n217: - [ ] Test `GetSandboxBySessionID()` returns `ErrNotFound` for missing key\n218: - [ ] Test `GetSandboxBySessionID()` rejects empty sessionID\n219: - [ ] Test `StoreSandbox()` validation (nil, empty ID, zero ExpiresAt)\n220: - [ ] Test `StoreSandbox()` atomic pipeline execution\n221: - [ ] Test `StoreSandbox()` fails on duplicate session\n222: - [ ] Test `UpdateSandbox()` XX flag behavior (missing key fails)\n223: - [ ] Test `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` removes all keys\n224: - [ ] Test `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` rejects empty sessionID\n225: - [ ] Test `ListExpiredSandboxes()` limit <= 0 returns empty\n226: - [ ] Test `ListExpiredSandboxes()` skips orphaned entries\n227: - [ ] Test `ListInactiveSandboxes()` functionality\n228: - [ ] Test `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` returns `ErrNotFound` for missing session\n229: - [ ] Test `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` zero time uses now\n230: - [ ] Test `Close()` releases connection\n231: - **Verification:** `go test ./pkg/store/... -run TestRedis` passes\n232: - **Files:** `pkg/store/redis_test.go`\n233: \n234: ### T23: Unit Tests - Valkey Implementation [PENDING]\n235: - [ ] Test all scenarios from T22 adapted for Valkey\n236: - [ ] Test `IsValkeyNil` error translation to `ErrNotFound`\n237: - [ ] Test comma-separated address parsing (`VALKEY_ADDR`)\n238: - [ ] Test `DisableCache` option when `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n239: - [ ] Test `ForceSingleClient` option when `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n240: - **Verification:** `go test ./pkg/store/... -run TestValkey` passes\n241: - **Files:** `pkg/store/valkey_test.go`\n242: \n243: ### T24: Unit Tests - Singleton & Configuration [PENDING]\n244: - [ ] Test concurrent `Storage()` calls return same instance\n245: - [ ] Test `STORE_TYPE` case-insensitive (REDIS, Valkey, etc.)\n246: - [ ] Test default to Redis when `STORE_TYPE` unset\n247: - [ ] Test invalid `STORE_TYPE` fails initialization\n248: - [ ] Test Redis config: missing `REDIS_ADDR` fails\n249: - [ ] Test Redis config: password required by default\n250: - [ ] Test Redis config: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` allows empty password\n251: - [ ] Test Valkey config: missing `VALKEY_ADDR` fails\n252: - [ ] Test Valkey config: password required by default\n253: - [ ] Test Valkey config: `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` allows empty password\n254: - **Verification:** `go test ./pkg/store/... -run TestSingleton` passes\n255: - **Files:** `pkg/store/singleton_test.go`\n256: \n257: ### T25: Dependencies & Build [PENDING]\n258: - [ ] Add `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` to go.mod\n259: - [ ] Add `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` to go.mod\n260: - [ ] Run `go mod tidy`\n261: - [ ] Verify build: `go build ./pkg/store/...`\n262: - **Verification:** No build errors; imports resolve\n263: - **Files:** `go.mod`, `go.sum`\n264: \n265: ### T26: Integration Tests [PENDING]\n266: - [ ] Create `pkg/store/redis_integration_test.go` with testcontainers\n267: - [ ] Test end-to-end Redis CRUD operations\n268: - [ ] Create `pkg/store/valkey_integration_test.go` with testcontainers\n269: - [ ] Test end-to-end Valkey CRUD operations\n270: - [ ] Test concurrent access safety\n271: - [ ] Test index consistency (ZSETs maintained correctly)\n272: - **Verification:** Integration tests pass with real Redis/Valkey\n273: - **Files:** `pkg/store/*_integration_test.go`\n274: \n275: ### T27: Documentation [PENDING]\n276: - [ ] Add package-level GoDoc for `pkg/store`\n277: - [ ] Document `redisStore` struct and methods\n278: - [ ] Document `valkeyStore` struct and methods\n279: - [ ] Add usage examples in code comments\n280: - **Verification:** `go doc ./pkg/store` displays properly\n281: - **Files:** `pkg/store/redis.go`, `pkg/store/valkey.go`, `pkg/store/singleton.go`\n282: \n283: ## Verification Commands\n284: \n285: ```bash\n286: # Build verification\n287: go build ./pkg/store/...\n288: \n289: # Unit test verification\n290: go test ./pkg/store/... -v\n291: \n292: # Race detection\n293: go test ./pkg/store/... -race\n294: \n295: # Coverage report\n296: go test ./pkg/store/... -cover\n297: \n298: # Integration tests (requires Docker)\n299: go test ./pkg/store/... -tags=integration -v\n300: ```\n301: \n302: ## Dependencies\n303: \n304: - AR-012: Store interface definition (`pkg/store/store.go`)\n305: - `pkg/common/types` for `SandboxInfo` type\n306: - `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`\n307: - `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n308: \n309: ## Notes\n310: \n311: - Design completed in Stage ST-3\n312: - Redis and Valkey implementations are independent - can be done in parallel\n313: - All store operations must be atomic (use pipelines/multi)\n314: - Orphan tolerance: list operations skip missing keys without failing\n315: - Error translation: backend-specific nil errors → `ErrNotFound`\n316: - Key naming: `session:{id}` format consistently\n317: - Index keys: `session:expiry`, `session:last_activity`\n\n(End of file - total 317 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-013 Tasks: Redis 存储实现 (Redis Storage Implementation)\n\n## Overview\n- **AR:** AR-013\n- **Module:** pkg/store\n- **Language:** Go\n- **Size:** M\n- **Status:** Stage ST-3 (Design) Completed\n- **Base Spec:** AR-012 (Store Interface Definition)\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### T1: Redis Store Implementation - Core Stru