{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869871235,"sessionID":"ses_285eaae91ffe60KoaOG4ouBHAC","part":{"id":"prt_d7a16b95d001tlmKMGyV59lgU1","messageID":"msg_d7a169539001IS2p29YLXZB2aY","sessionID":"ses_285eaae91ffe60KoaOG4ouBHAC","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:16","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md","content":"# AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 (Valkey Storage Implementation)\n\n> **Module:** `pkg/store`  \n> **Language:** Go  \n> **Size:** S  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)  \n> **Base Spec:** AR-012 (Store Interface Definition)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nAR-014 implements a Valkey-backed storage provider for the Store interface defined in AR-012. Valkey is an open-source Redis fork that provides high-performance key-value storage with clustering support. This implementation uses the `valkey-go` client library.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.1 — Valkey Store Core Structure\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.1.1 | Create `pkg/store/valkey.go` with `valkeyStore` struct | File compiles; `go build ./pkg/store/...` succeeds | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.2 | Define `valkeyOptions` struct with `InitAddress []string`, `Password`, `DisableCache`, `ForceSingleClient` | Struct fields align with valkey-go ClientOption | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.3 | Implement `newValkeyStore()` constructor | Returns Store interface implementation | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.4 | Implement `makeValkeyOptions()` for environment parsing | `VALKEY_ADDR`, `VALKEY_PASSWORD`, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED`, `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE`, `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.5 | Add `sessionKey()` helper method for key construction | Returns `session:{id}` format | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Valkey store structure compiles with proper configuration.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.2 — Valkey Core Store Methods\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.2.1 | Implement `Ping(ctx context.Context) error` | Returns nil on \"PONG\" response; returns error on failure | 0.5h |\n| 4.2.2 | Implement `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)` | Returns `ErrNotFound` for missing keys; validates empty sessionID | 1h |\n| 4.2.3 | Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error` | Uses `DoMulti` atomic operation: SET NX + ZADD expiry + ZADD last_activity | 1h |\n| 4.2.4 | Implement `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error` | Uses SET XX flag; returns error if key doesn't exist | 0.5h |\n| 4.2.5 | Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) error` | Uses `DoMulti` atomic: DEL + ZREM expiry + ZREM last_activity | 0.5h |\n| 4.2.6 | Implement `Close() error` | Calls `s.cli.Close()`; returns nil | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** All core CRUD operations work with Valkey backend.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.3 — Valkey Index Management Methods\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.3.1 | Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` | Uses `ZRANGEBYSCORE` on `session:expiry`; returns nil if limit <= 0 | 1h |\n| 4.3.2 | Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` | Uses `ZRANGEBYSCORE` on `session:last_activity` | 1h |\n| 4.3.3 | Implement `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` helper | Uses `MGET` for batch fetch; skips orphaned entries gracefully | 1h |\n| 4.3.4 | Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID string, at time.Time) error` | Checks EXISTS first; uses `time.Now()` if at.IsZero() | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Index operations support session lifecycle management.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.4 — Valkey Error Handling\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.4.1 | Translate `valkey.IsValkeyNil()` to `ErrNotFound` | Unit test: missing key returns `ErrNotFound` | 0.5h |\n| 4.4.2 | Handle SET NX failure (session already exists) | Returns \"session already exists\" error | 0.5h |\n| 4.4.3 | Handle SET XX failure (key not exists) | Returns \"key not exists\" error | 0.5h |\n| 4.4.4 | Handle `DoMulti` partial failures | Returns error from first failed command | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Error handling consistent with Redis implementation.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.5 — Unit Tests — Valkey Implementation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.5.1 | Write `TestValkeyStore_Ping` — success and failure | Mock valkey-go client; verify \"PONG\" parsing | 1h |\n| 4.5.2 | Write `TestValkeyStore_GetSandboxBySessionID` — validation, not found, success | Verify `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` translation | 1h |\n| 4.5.3 | Write `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox` — validation (nil, empty ID, zero ExpiresAt), success, duplicate | Verify atomic `DoMulti` with SET NX + ZADD x2 | 1.5h |\n| 4.5.4 | Write `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox` — validation, missing key, success | Verify SET XX behavior | 1h |\n| 4.5.5 | Write `TestValkeyStore_DeleteSandboxBySessionID` — validation, success, idempotent | Verify atomic cleanup of session + indexes | 1h |\n| 4.5.6 | Write `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes` — limit <= 0, expired sessions, limit applied | Verify `ZRANGEBYSCORE` + `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` | 1h |\n| 4.5.7 | Write `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes` — inactive sessions | Similar to expired tests | 1h |\n| 4.5.8 | Write `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity` — validation, not found, zero time, specific time | Verify EXISTS check + ZADD | 1h |\n| 4.5.9 | Write `TestValkeyStore_LoadSandboxesBySessionIDs` — empty, orphaned entries, batch load | Verify MGET + orphan skipping | 1h |\n| 4.5.10 | Write `TestValkeyStore_Close` — connection release | Verify `cli.Close()` called | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** `go test ./pkg/store/... -run TestValkey` passes with >80% coverage.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.6 — Unit Tests — Configuration\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.6.1 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_MissingAddr` — error when VALKEY_ADDR unset | Returns error | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.2 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_PasswordRequired` — error when password required but missing | Returns error | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.3 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_PasswordOptional` — success when VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false | Allows empty password | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.4 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_MultipleAddresses` — comma-separated VALKEY_ADDR parsing | Splits and trims addresses | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.5 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_DisableCache` — parse VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE | Sets DisableCache field | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.6 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_ForceSingle` — parse VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE | Sets ForceSingleClient field | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.7 | Write `TestNewValkeyStore` — integration with makeValkeyOptions | Returns valid Store interface | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Configuration tests pass with environment variable isolation.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.7 — Integration Tests\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.7.1 | Create `pkg/store/valkey_integration_test.go` with testcontainers | Setup real Valkey container | 1.5h |\n| 4.7.2 | Write end-to-end CRUD test — full lifecycle | Store → Get → Update → Delete | 1h |\n| 4.7.3 | Write index consistency test | Verify ZSETs maintained correctly | 1h |\n| 4.7.4 | Write concurrent access safety test | 10 concurrent operations, no race | 1h |\n| 4.7.5 | Write orphaned entry tolerance test | Delete session data, verify list skips gracefully | 1h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Integration tests pass with real Valkey instance.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.8 — Documentation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.8.1 | Add package-level GoDoc for valkey.go | `go doc ./pkg/store` shows Valkey implementation | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.2 | Document `valkeyStore` struct with inline comments | Clear explanation of fields | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.3 | Document each method with purpose and behavior | Godoc format comments | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.4 | Add environment variable documentation | List all VALKEY_* variables | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Code is well-documented for future maintainers.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| Phase | Tasks | Est. Hours |\n|-------|-------|------------|\n| ST-4.1: Core Structure | 5 | 2.25h |\n| ST-4.2: Core Methods | 6 | 3.75h |\n| ST-4.3: Index Management | 4 | 3h |\n| ST-4.4: Error Handling | 4 | 2h |\n| ST-4.5: Unit Tests (Valkey) | 10 | 10h |\n| ST-4.6: Unit Tests (Config) | 7 | 3.5h |\n| ST-4.7: Integration Tests | 5 | 5.5h |\n| ST-4.8: Documentation | 4 | 2h |\n| **Total** | **45** | **32h** |\n\n---\n\n## File Deliverables Checklist\n\n- [ ] `pkg/store/valkey.go` — Valkey Store implementation\n- [ ] `pkg/store/valkey_test.go` — Valkey unit tests\n- [ ] `pkg/store/valkey_integration_test.go` — Valkey integration tests\n\n---\n\n## Verification Commands\n\n```bash\n# Build verification\ngo build ./pkg/store/...\n\n# Unit test verification (all store tests)\ngo test ./pkg/store/... -v\n\n# Valkey-specific tests\ngo test ./pkg/store/... -run TestValkey -v\n\n# Configuration tests\ngo test ./pkg/store/... -run TestMakeValkey -v\n\n# Race detection\ngo test ./pkg/store/... -race\n\n# Coverage report\ngo test ./pkg/store/... -cover\n\n# Integration tests (requires Docker)\ngo test ./pkg/store/... -tags=integration -v\n```\n\n---\n\n## Definition of Done\n\n- [ ] All 45 tasks complete\n- [ ] `valkeyStore` implements full `Store` interface\n- [ ] Unit tests pass (>80% coverage for valkey.go)\n- [ ] Configuration tests pass\n- [ ] Integration tests pass with real Valkey\n- [ ] Race detector clean\n- [ ] `go build ./pkg/store/...` succeeds\n- [ ] Documentation complete with GoDoc\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- AR-012: Store interface definition (`pkg/store/store.go`)\n- AR-013: Redis implementation (reference patterns)\n- `pkg/common/types` for `SandboxInfo` type\n- `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` v1.0.56\n\n---\n\n## Design Notes\n\n- **Key naming:** Uses `session:{id}` prefix consistently\n- **Index keys:** `session:expiry`, `session:last_activity` (sorted sets)\n- **Atomic operations:** Uses `DoMulti` for multi-command atomicity\n- **Orphan tolerance:** List operations skip missing keys without failing\n- **Error translation:** `valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)` → `ErrNotFound`\n- **Configuration:** Follows same pattern as Redis with VALKEY_* env vars\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/redis.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/store.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/valkey.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/go.mod":[{"range":{"start":{"line":18,"character":42},"end":{"line":18,"character":53}},"severity":2,"source":"go mod tidy","message":"github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2 should be direct"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/singleton.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/redis_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":38,"character":26},"end":{"line":38,"character":38}},"severity":3,"code":"unusedparams","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/unusedparams#unusedparams"},"source":"unusedparams","message":"unused parameter: t"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/store_test.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md","exi